# Anti-Homogenization — Constraints

## Principle
Copy that any competitor could use without changing = GENERIC = FAILED.

## Logo Test
Replace your brand with competitor's. If copy still works → FAIL.
Every deliverable MUST pass Logo Test before delivery.

## Banned Words (NEVER use)
revolucionario, inovador, incrivel, transformador, exclusivo,
desbloqueie, jornada, potencialize, empoderamento, holístico,
sinergia, paradigma, disruptivo, game-changer, breakthrough

## Banned Patterns
- "Imagine [generic benefit]..." without sensory specifics
- "E se eu te dissesse que..." (overused pattern)
- "O segredo que [authority] nao quer que voce saiba" (unless true)
- Generic testimonials without names and specifics
- Future pacing without sight + sound + physical sensation

## Required Instead
- Avatar's EXACT language from VOC (not paraphrase)
- Sinestesia da rotina: specific moment from THIS avatar's daily life
- Sensory details: what they see, hear, feel physically
- Fragments > complete sentences (when impact is greater)
- Conversation > formal writing
- Absolute language, zero hesitation

## DRE-First in Every Element
- Hook: DRE in first sentence (not second)
- Body: DRE escalates from level 2 to level 4
- CTA: DRE at peak (level 4-5) to drive action
- Subject line: DRE-loaded, not clever

## Per-Creative Diversity
No two creatives from same batch should use:
- Same opening structure
- Same angle
- Same format
- Same DRE entry point
